item.title: In defence of Objective-C - chrisfromsydney's posterous
item.dc:creator: hmans
item.description: Obj-C was born in the 80’s, when programming was simple. The architecture astronautitis (Java) that is all too common these days was nowhere to be seen, and it shows. It is the simplest possible OO layer on top of plain old C. Pragmatism rules the day in a lot of the design decisions, and i’ve found it is a great language for Getting Stuff Done, if not in the prettiest way possible. I like to think of it as a simple, reliable old car that just keeps going.
